cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a deep generative model for analyzing neuroimaging data, which involves both machine learning and neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the usefulness of the inferred latent factor representations for downstream tasks such as multivoxel pattern analysis and functional connectivity, which suggests relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
